08/06/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- During a visit to the OSCE Mission in Zagreb on Tuesday (7 June), Prime Minister Ivo Sanader reaffirmed that reconciliation, co-operation with the UN tribunal, return of refugees, restitution of property and Euro-Atlantic integration are government priorities and the "right path" for the country. Sanader told OSCE Mission Chief Jorge Fuentes Monzonis-Vilallonga that Zagreb is working to normalise relations with Serbia-Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina, as this was key to stabilising the region. (Vecernji list - 08/06/05; HINA - 07/06/05)
